sub_title: Hello! this is Seojeong Park :) I'm a mainly Graphic designer, I'm into Character designing & digital painting, Korean & English speaker
summary:
Intership at Toytron as a Graphic designer (SEP 2018 - Nov 2018)
-Toytron is one of the top toy companies for children in South Korea. while intership, I designed web banners and thumbnails for the web shop, managing products and the web shop. also collecting orders and did customer services too.

Worked as a Graphic designer at Jinyeong global (Nob 2018 - Jun 2019)
-Jinyeong global is a plush doll company of South Korea. I've designed thumbnails and images for the details of products on the web shop, and I managed the web shops. also designed plush dolls and fancy products. I worked on the project that made some of the famous Korean emoji's into plush dolls on the Korean Go fund me like site.

Intership at C&H Creative as a Product designer (Jun 2019 - Aug 2019)
-C&H Creative is a Plush doll company which has licenses from Disney and Universal pictures. I designed plush slippers with 'How to train your dragon' and 'Minions' characters on it, key chains and plush dolls for 'Frozen 2' franchise and etc..

Worked as a Main designer at Kikakuv (Nov 2019 - Dec 2020)
-Kikakuv is a custom figure doll Start-up. I did so much of things while I worked there as a Main designer. first and all I designed every visual contents for the company such as a promotion images for Instagram and Korean version of Etsy. and Images For the products and managing the web shops and did the customer services. customer service and communicating with customer was so important in this company, because it's all about customizing whatever they wanted and meant. and my customers are always satisfied with their results. after designing clothes, I also built the figure dolls too -to building that figure dolls, I had to deeply experience with UV printing. every designed clothing is printed on the figure. which requires good understanding of printing and vector images.
